<subSubSection id="C324329FFF941179FF44DA69CBE92EE3" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B816114FF941179FF44DA69CBE92EE3" blockId="1.[151,1437,706,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="B94ABD06FF941179FF44DA69C96B2E5A" bold="true" box="[199,321,814,839]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons flat, subtly concave anteriorly; mandibles dorsally and laterally concave and longer than frons and clypeus together; cavity for insertion of antennal club deep, well defined; marginal stria of prosternal lobe complete and laterally represented by three sulci; marginal pronotal stria complete laterally, united with the anterior marginal stria behind the head; elytra with dorsal and subhumeral striae deeply impressed, 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FA8DDAD9CD362EAB" box="[1294,1308,926,950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
st– 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FAB7DAD9CD6B2EAB" box="[1332,1345,926,950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="4.0">4</number>
th dorsal striae complete, inner subhumeral united with oblique humeral stria; anterior, middle and hind femora robust, tibiae broad; propygidium coarsely punctuated on the sides; pygidium smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C324329FFF94117BFF44DD4ECC292816" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="440" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B816114FF941179FF44DD4ECCA02AEE" blockId="1.[151,1437,706,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="B94ABD06FF941179FF44DD4EC973293F" bold="true" box="[199,345,1033,1058]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">Description.</emphasis>
(pronotum+elytra) 
<quantity id="4CC6CCF1FF941179FDB8DD4DCA92293C" box="[571,696,1034,1058]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11 mm</quantity>
, elytral width (humeral region): 
<quantity id="4CC6CCF1FF941179FBB0DD4DCCBC293C" box="[1075,1174,1034,1058]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9 mm</quantity>
. Cuticular color black. Body shape oval, glabrous (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FE54DD6ACA31295B" box="[471,539,1069,1094]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FD8EDD69CA31295B" box="[525,539,1070,1094]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A–C). Frons flat, subtly concave anteriorly; frontal stria strong and complete; supraorbital stria absent; frontoclypeal suture absent; epistoma slightly concave medially; mandibles concave dorsally and laterally, longer than the frons and epistoma together (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FC25DD32CBC62993" box="[934,1004,1141,1166]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FC5DDD31CBC62993" box="[990,1004,1142,1166]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D); postoccipital stria complete with setae; postgena with a fovea. Antennae with scapus slender at the base; antennal club with distinct apical sensorial area, basal pseudo-suture straight, apical pseudo-suture represented by small sensorial points. Submentum subpentagonal with few setae on the surface. Prothorax, cavity for insertion of antennal club deep, well defined, broadly open beneath; prosternal lobe about 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FD0CDC41CAB32803" box="[655,665,1286,1310]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FD27DC41CA982803" box="[676,690,1286,1310]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="3.0">3</number>
of the total length of prosternum, anterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FADADC42CDB62803" box="[1369,1436,1285,1310]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FA0DDC41CDB62803" box="[1422,1436,1286,1310]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B), marginal stria complete and laterally represented by three sulci (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FC37DC6ECBD0285F" box="[948,1018,1321,1346]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FC6FDC6DCBD0285F" box="[1004,1018,1322,1346]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B); lateral marginal prosternal stria complete; prosternal keel without stria and the posterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FC48DC0ACC26287B" box="[971,1036,1357,1382]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FC7DDC09CC26287B" box="[1022,1036,1358,1382]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Pronotum, anterior margin with a medial pronotal and anterolateral gland openings; marginal stria complete laterally, united with the anterior marginal behind the head; outer lateral stria rounding the anterior corners ending freely; inner lateral stria complete along the sides and front, joined by the marginal, sometimes vanishing on the anterior angles. Elytra, longer than 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FF14DC9AC89328EB" box="[151,185,1501,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.5">1.5</number>
x the length of pronotum, without depression at the sutural and posterior region (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FB1BDC9ACCCB28EB" box="[1176,1249,1501,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FB50DC99CCCB28EB" box="[1235,1249,1502,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A); dorsal and subhumeral striae deeply impressed, except the oblique humeral stria; 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FC35DF42CBEE2B00" box="[950,964,1541,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
st– 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FC5FDF42CBC32B00" box="[988,1001,1541,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="4.0">4</number>
th dorsal striae complete, 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FA86DF43CD392B00" box="[1285,1299,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="5.0">5</number>
th dorsal and sutural striae present only on posterior half, the last one shorter (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FCFBDF6FCB962B5D" box="[888,956,1576,1601]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FC2DDF6FCB962B5D" box="[942,956,1576,1600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A); inner subhumeral united with oblique humeral stria; outer subhumeral stria present on anterior half; epipleural region with three striae, the first short and marked on the anterior region, the second and third striae derived from a single branch and ramified in the posterior half of the elytra. Mesoventrite with anterior margin emarginate medially; marginal stria complete; mesometaventral stria absent (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FE69DFFFCA062BCD" box="[490,556,1720,1745]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FD9DDFFFCA062BCD" box="[542,556,1720,1744]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Metaventrite with lateral metaventral stria curved outward extending up to the middle of metasternal-metepisternal suture, postmesocoxal stria present (
<figureCitation id="13057D91FF941179FC7DDF9BCC682BE8" box="[1022,1090,1756,1781]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,195,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hister lucia sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Lateral view; D. Frontal view; E. Propygidium and Pygidium (scales: A – C = 2 mm; D – E = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241369/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FBB7DF9ACC682BE8" box="[1076,1090,1757,1781]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Anterior, middle and hind femora and tibiae robust, the middle and hind almost parallel sided. Anterior leg, femora with setae on the anterior surface and a row of setae on the outer margin; apical margin of tibiae truncated, wider than femora, outer margin with three-four teeth adorned with spines or not, inner submarginal and marginal striae complete, the last one adorned with setae, tarsal cavities straight; thickness of the tarsus similar of tibial spurs. Middle and hind tibiae, outer margin with two series of short denticles adorned with spines longer than denticles; inner margin with marginal and submarginal striae; tarsus thicker than the tibial spurs. Stria of 
<number id="3DF67333FF941179FC75DEF0CC2E2AD2" box="[1014,1028,1975,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
st visible abdominal sternum marked only laterally. Propygidium coarsely punctuated on the sides. Pygidium smooth (
